The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Gautam named best cricketer
                                                                                                                       7                                      Gautam named best cricketer
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: India opener Gautam Gambhir will receive the Polly Umrigar Award for being Indias best international cricketer of the year at the annual BCCI Awards Ceremony for the year 2008-09. The ceremony will be held on December 6, at the East Lawns of the Cricket Club of India in Mumbai.         
	The best performers in Indian cricket during the period from October 1, 2008 to September 30, 2009, will be honoured and rewarded.         
	Sachin Tendulkar will receive a special memento for completing 20 years in international cricket. Rahul Dravid would be felicitated for creating a world record in the number of catches held in Tests.         
	A highlight of the ceremony will be the celebration of the Platinum Jubilee of the Ranji Trophy. Mohinder Amarnath, a key member of the 1983 World Cup-winning team, will receive the prestigious CK Nayudu Lifetime Achievement Award.         
	The ICC international panel umpire Amish Saheba will be the first winner of the newly-instituted Best Umpire Award.                                                                                                                     
